<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.61334/95a</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bading</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1923</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. Jordan Herbert Stabler is proceeding
                            to Ecuador in the interest of the Mercantile Bank of the Americas in
                            connection with the matter pending between the bank and the Asociación
                            de Agriculture [<hi rend="italic">Agricultores</hi>] del Ecuador. You
                            are requested to render Mr. Stabler all appropriate assistance in the
                            transaction of his business.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Leland
                                    Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>